name: Mystery Canyon
description:
Introduction

One of the most coveted canyons in Zion, one of the most difficult permits to get. There is a two-stage lottery for permits. Extreme good luck required to get a weekend permit, but weekday ones are much easier.

This canyons will seem spectacular or mediocre depending on the time of the day you visit it. When the sun is at an angle is when you will experience the canyon glowing with its best colors.

Try to time your arrival at the big rappel for either mid-afternoon or mid-morning.

Approach

Two approaches are available. One can hike up from Zion Canyon / Weeping Rock shuttle stop; or drive around to the East Mesa Trailhead on the Ponderosa Ranch Resort and hike a flat trail to the head of the canyon. The second requires a one-hour each-way car fetch, or using a commercial shuttle from Springdale.

Descent

Mystery canyon is noted for the variety of terrain it offers.

The adventure starts with a steep descent down "The Death Gully" (no deaths reported to date). It is important to find the correct small trail, as off-trail descent of this slope is gruesome. Descend the Death Gully. Hike down the wooded canyon floor with a few short downclimbs. (A bolt anchor is available at most of the downclimbs, for those who would prefer a short rappel.) At the end of the wooded canyon is the Rock Narrows, a series of about six rappels one after the other. All anchors are two-bolt anchors.

After the Rock Narrows, the canyon widens and becomes wooded again. A brief walk leads to the Mystery Canyon seasonal lake, which is a dry or muddy flat unless it has rained in the last few days. A three hundred foot pile of sand and rocks blocks the canyon, creating the lake. Climb the sand pile on the right margin, then down the other side. A bit more hiking, a rappel and a few downclimbs leads to the spectacular final section.

An easy but exposed walk out to a bolt anchor (safety line usually in place) leads to a rappel into Mystery Springs and a two-stroke swim. The canyon has a small flow from this point. A couple slimy downclimbs including into a short swim leads to the final rappel next to Mystery Falls into The Narrows.

Exit

Walk down The Narrows about 20 minutes to the paved trail, then 20 minutes to the Temple of Sinawava shuttle stop.

Red tape

This canyon requires a permit, and it is one of the most difficult permits to get.

properties.name: Weeping Rock Shuttle Stop
properties.description: Due to a massive rock fall in 2019 that has indefinitely closed the lower portion of the East Rim Trail, it is not currently possible to approach Mystery Canyon via this route from begging at this shuttle stop.  Currently the long, drive-around route from the East Mesa Trailhead is the only practical way to run Mystery Canyon.

properties.name: East Mesa Trailhead Parking
properties.description: Leave a starting vehicle here to be recovered later on.  Or, better yet get dropped off here.  It is worth it to hire a guide company to drop you off so you don't have to recover a vehicle later on.

properties.name: East Rim Trail
properties.description: This section of the East Rim Trail is open, but due to the lower section being indefinitely closed, it is not possible to use this as part of the approach from Zion Canyon itself.

properties.name: East Rim Trail - Indefinitely Closed
properties.description: Due to a massive rock fall in 2019 this portion of the East Rim Trail has been closed indefinitely.  It may be decades--if ever--before this section of trail is open again.  Consequently, it is not currently possible to approach Mystery Canyon via this route from. Currently the long, drive-around route from the East Mesa Trailhead is the only practical way to run Mystery Canyon.

properties.name: Several Rappels
properties.description: There are several rappels in this section of the canyon.

properties.name: Exit Vehicle Parking
properties.description: Leave a vehicle here--or in town--to be used upon exit.  You will either need to drive back up and recover the start vehicle, or if you got dropped off at the start trailhead you can use this vehicle to drive home.
